verses.roman:
"ki mora kartavya, muñi nā jāni uddeśa
āpani śrī-mukhe more kara upadeśa"

synonyms: ki—what; mora kartavya—my duty; muñi—I; nā jāni—do not know; uddeśa—the goal of my life; āpani—personally; śrī-mukhe—through Your transcendental mouth; more—unto me; kara upadeśa—please give instructions.
translation: "I do not know my duty or the goal of my life. Therefore, please personally give me instructions from Your transcendental mouth.' "
